433
00:23:57,000 --> 00:23:59,079
I might draw a slightly smaller loop.

434
00:23:59,359 --> 00:24:00,319
I think that's enough.

435
00:24:06,680 --> 00:24:08,000
The joy of this,

436
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:10,440
isn't really about the race.

437
00:24:10,440 --> 00:24:12,920
It's about the feeling and the connection we have,

438
00:24:12,920 --> 00:24:15,720
with the mountains and with nature.

439
00:24:15,720 --> 00:24:17,880
That's really it. Yeah.

440
00:24:17,880 --> 00:24:20,519
So I'd love to come back and feel that again,

441
00:24:20,519 --> 00:24:23,000
either on my own,

442
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:25,720
or with friends, designing our own routes.

443
00:24:56,559 --> 00:24:59,000
I can't say exactly,

444
00:24:59,720 --> 00:25:02,000
whether there were any big things I was thinking through

445
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:03,000
while I was climbing.

446
00:25:03,279 --> 00:25:07,599
There are a few things I can remember now,

447
00:25:07,599 --> 00:25:08,839
nothing especially interesting,

448
00:25:08,839 --> 00:25:10,279
but I'll say them anyway.

449
00:25:10,720 --> 00:25:12,960
One thing I noticed,

450
00:25:12,960 --> 00:25:13,839
especially during the day,

451
00:25:15,920 --> 00:25:19,680
was just how many people were out in the mountains.

452
00:25:19,839 --> 00:25:20,640
Older people,

453
00:25:20,640 --> 00:25:22,559
young people, children, families,

454
00:25:22,559 --> 00:25:24,519
hiking, running, all of it.

455
00:25:24,519 --> 00:25:25,279
I just thought, wow,

456
00:25:25,279 --> 00:25:28,960
the outdoor culture here is so rich. It's really impressive.

457
00:25:30,960 --> 00:25:32,839
So the title of this film,

458
00:25:32,839 --> 00:25:34,799
Ephemeral Mountains,

459
00:25:34,799 --> 00:25:36,119
what does that mean to you?

460
00:25:36,960 --> 00:25:38,000
Ephemeral?

461
00:25:38,279 --> 00:25:40,559
As in "Ephemeral Mountains"?

462
00:25:41,559 --> 00:25:43,400
I don't really buy that.

463
00:25:43,680 --> 00:25:45,640
I don't feel anything ephemeral right now,

464
00:25:45,640 --> 00:25:48,680
because they're hitting me in the face every day.

465
00:25:49,720 --> 00:25:51,200
It feels very, very real,

466
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:52,240
and very hard.

467
00:25:54,880 --> 00:25:57,839
Obviously, if you train really hard,

468
00:25:57,839 --> 00:26:00,279
like Hai Guai does.

469
00:26:00,279 --> 00:26:02,720
But as I said before, for Hai Guai,

470
00:26:02,720 --> 00:26:04,680
I don't even think of it as training, exactly.

471
00:26:04,680 --> 00:26:08,400
It's not like he follows some training calendar.

472
00:26:09,279 --> 00:26:10,400
That's just what he does.

473
00:26:10,720 --> 00:26:11,079
But, you know,

474
00:26:11,079 --> 00:26:12,920
he spends a lot of time in the mountains,

475
00:26:12,920 --> 00:26:14,599
and that naturally makes you faster.

476
00:26:15,039 --> 00:26:17,440
But I think the core skill here,

477
00:26:17,440 --> 00:26:20,839
is really understanding your body.

478
00:26:20,839 --> 00:26:24,880
If you know how much water, salt, and food

479
00:26:26,000 --> 00:26:26,960
your body needs,

480
00:26:26,960 --> 00:26:30,119
and you can actually digest it properly,

481
00:26:30,119 --> 00:26:32,400
then you can just keep going. Sleep matters too,

482
00:26:32,400 --> 00:26:34,599
and that's the part I struggle with.

483
00:26:41,640 --> 00:26:43,960
I never really wanted it to end.

484
00:26:43,960 --> 00:26:45,720
I just wanted to keep going,

485
00:26:45,720 --> 00:26:48,960
keep climbing, even on that last climb.

486
00:26:50,279 --> 00:26:51,880
I felt full of energy.

487
00:26:51,880 --> 00:26:53,400
Honestly, I would've been happy

488
00:26:53,400 --> 00:26:55,799
if that climb had gone on for another thousand meters.

489
00:26:57,839 --> 00:26:59,720
You're still smiling.

490
00:27:01,559 --> 00:27:06,279
I don't know, it just feels good. And the views are amazing.

491
00:27:06,279 --> 00:27:08,079
It's not just the view from the top,

492
00:27:08,079 --> 00:27:11,039
it's the view every hundred meters.

493
00:27:11,039 --> 00:27:13,240
Every few hundred meters, it's different.

494
00:27:13,240 --> 00:27:15,079
I'd been waiting for it for

495
00:27:15,079 --> 00:27:17,160
all 330 kilometers, and honestly,

496
00:27:17,160 --> 00:27:21,480
when I reached the last pass,

497
00:27:22,200 --> 00:27:25,000
I was sad it was the last one.

498
00:27:25,279 --> 00:27:27,160
I didn't want it to be the last.

499
00:27:27,160 --> 00:27:29,359
It's strange to think that was the final climb.

500
00:27:35,880 --> 00:27:38,240
And it feels really special.

501
00:27:38,640 --> 00:27:42,440
And I guess when I get back to normal life,

502
00:27:42,480 --> 00:27:47,559
I'm going to miss that feeling of

503
00:27:49,359 --> 00:27:50,319
pushing my body,

504
00:27:50,319 --> 00:27:52,319
and feeling that connection with nature.

505
00:27:58,359 --> 00:28:00,240
Okay, thank you.

506
00:28:05,480 --> 00:28:09,200
If you want something hot, soup, tea, coffee...

507
00:28:09,200 --> 00:28:10,079
Okay.

508
00:28:11,480 --> 00:28:12,839
What would you like?

509
00:28:14,400 --> 00:28:15,200
Okay.

510
00:28:16,799 --> 00:28:19,200
Perfect, thank you. Bye.

511
00:28:19,200 --> 00:28:21,599
Thank you too.

512
00:28:26,839 --> 00:28:28,319
It's ephemeral.

513
00:28:28,319 --> 00:28:30,119
I can really feel that now.

514
00:28:30,359 --> 00:28:32,240
It feels like a long time while you're inside it.

515
00:28:32,240 --> 00:28:33,960
Even after the first night,

516
00:28:33,960 --> 00:28:36,279
I felt like I couldn't even imagine

517
00:28:36,279 --> 00:28:37,319
there were still three days left.

518
00:28:37,960 --> 00:28:40,400
But the moment you stop thinking about it,

519
00:28:40,400 --> 00:28:41,440
you can hardly feel it at all.

520
00:28:41,440 --> 00:28:43,720
You just keep moving, and suddenly it's over.

521
00:28:49,119 --> 00:28:50,519
After climbing so many mountains,

522
00:28:50,880 --> 00:28:52,400
do you still like climbing?

523
00:28:52,400 --> 00:28:53,200
Of course.

524
00:28:53,200 --> 00:28:55,599
I'm already looking forward to the next one.

525
00:29:02,079 --> 00:29:03,039
After climbing that many mountains,

526
00:29:03,519 --> 00:29:05,440
I still don't feel tired of climbing.

527
00:29:07,960 --> 00:29:08,920
Today was so long.

528
00:29:09,519 --> 00:29:10,640
I feel like I've been climbing forever.

529
00:29:13,200 --> 00:29:15,119
All that pain is just your brain talking.

530
00:29:15,119 --> 00:29:19,279
It's lying to you. It wants you back in the car.

531
00:29:21,359 --> 00:29:22,680
Maybe that moment is right now.

532
00:29:22,680 --> 00:29:24,119
I feel like I've only done one thing.

533
00:29:24,119 --> 00:29:24,799
That's all.

534
00:29:24,799 --> 00:29:25,839
But as for

535
00:29:25,839 --> 00:29:26,599
what it might mean,

536
00:29:26,599 --> 00:29:29,799
for my life in the future,

537
00:29:29,799 --> 00:29:30,640
maybe

538
00:29:30,839 --> 00:29:34,200
I'll only know when it happens.

539
00:29:37,559 --> 00:29:38,240
But for now,

540
00:29:38,240 --> 00:29:40,680
I don't think about it much.

541
00:29:40,920 --> 00:29:44,279
I don't think finishing this matters that much,

542
00:29:44,279 --> 00:29:45,359
or that it's something incredible.

543
00:29:45,359 --> 00:29:46,759
It's over now.

544
00:29:51,240 --> 00:29:54,200
A man with thunder in his chest and a calm face

545
00:29:55,000 --> 00:29:56,119
is fit to be a general.

546
00:29:56,319 --> 00:29:57,920
Right now, I'm all thunder inside,

547
00:29:58,519 --> 00:29:59,720
because the soles of my feet...

548
00:30:01,039 --> 00:30:02,640
it hurts like hell to walk on this road.

549
00:30:04,240 --> 00:30:05,279
Hai Guai and Bai Rui

550
00:30:05,279 --> 00:30:07,200
have finally completed their journey of giants.

551
00:30:07,920 --> 00:30:09,039
For us,

552
00:30:09,039 --> 00:30:10,200
the Alps are too far away,

553
00:30:10,599 --> 00:30:12,000
and 330 kilometers feels impossible.

554
00:30:12,880 --> 00:30:14,720
But the moment you step outside,

555
00:30:15,200 --> 00:30:17,039
nature is already right beside you.

556
00:30:48,839 --> 00:30:51,279
When you really come back, this is what it looks like.

557
00:30:51,279 --> 00:30:52,000
Maybe out there,

558
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:54,160
you imagined it countless times.

559
00:30:54,160 --> 00:30:55,359
I've imagined it countless times.

560
00:30:55,359 --> 00:30:58,640
That breakfast we had this morning,

561
00:31:01,519 --> 00:31:03,279
was the happiest moment.

562
00:31:03,279 --> 00:31:04,640
Maybe the happiest of the year.

563
00:31:04,640 --> 00:31:05,839
Happier than Spring Festival.

564
00:31:07,480 --> 00:31:08,839
How did you get up here?

565
00:31:09,960 --> 00:31:11,200
Can you drive halfway up?

566
00:31:11,200 --> 00:31:11,960
No, you can't.

567
00:31:11,960 --> 00:31:12,599
Oh my.

568
00:31:12,880 --> 00:31:13,680
We climbed all the way up here.

569
00:31:17,880 --> 00:31:18,960
You're the man, Director Jia.

570
00:31:27,640 --> 00:31:28,599
Call Xiaoqin.

571
00:31:28,759 --> 00:31:29,559
Call Xiaoqin.

572
00:31:42,559 --> 00:31:43,359
Here she comes.

573
00:31:49,839 --> 00:31:51,240
You're the best.
